343
00:19:30,651 --> 00:19:31,827
Showed no infection.

344
00:19:32,035 --> 00:19:34,602
So we still don't know
what caused her heart failure.

345
00:19:35,330 --> 00:19:37,022
Let's just be happy
she doesn't need a new heart.

346
00:19:37,106 --> 00:19:39,801
Mrs. Bardach, it could have
just been a one-time thing.

347
00:19:39,885 --> 00:19:42,013
So she has
an allergic reaction
and heart failure,

348
00:19:42,097 --> 00:19:43,944
and neither of them
can be explained.

349
00:19:45,068 --> 00:19:46,320
Are they doing
any more tests on her?

350
00:19:46,404 --> 00:19:48,134
- No.
- She's not here.

351
00:19:50,776 --> 00:19:54,693
Notify local hospitals, cab companies,
the state troopers, and local cops.

352
00:19:54,693 --> 00:19:57,197
Any security officers off duty
are back on duty.

353
00:19:57,260 --> 00:19:58,204
Woman:
<i>We're on it.</i>

354
00:19:58,288 --> 00:20:01,295
And I'm going to need some pictures.
And go through those drawers.

355
00:20:01,348 --> 00:20:04,746
And I want at least two people
going over the surveillance tapes.

356
00:20:04,839 --> 00:20:06,136
That work?

357
00:20:06,661 --> 00:20:07,932
Are those all her clothes?

358
00:20:08,016 --> 00:20:09,411
Uh, yeah.

359
00:20:09,690 --> 00:20:11,362
She's obviously
still in the building.

360
00:20:11,446 --> 00:20:13,247
So where did she go?
What does she want?

361
00:20:13,410 --> 00:20:14,903
See her boyfriend?

362
00:20:15,535 --> 00:20:17,199
She didn't take her phone.

363
00:20:17,940 --> 00:20:19,926
She wants to be outside.

364
00:20:32,758 --> 00:20:36,506
If you're trying to
scare your parents, great job.

365
00:20:37,945 --> 00:20:39,737
Can we go back now?

366
00:20:40,910 --> 00:20:42,586
I hate her.

367
00:20:44,481 --> 00:20:48,401
When I was eight years old,
I was sick.

368
00:20:48,628 --> 00:20:52,983
- Not really sick,
but the point is, my mom, she--
- She was like this before.

369
00:20:53,067 --> 00:20:56,914
Home by 9:00 every night.
Can't go out on the weekends.
Can't do sports.

370
00:20:57,281 --> 00:21:00,450
- Transplant just gave her
what she always wanted.
- Melinda...

371
00:21:00,534 --> 00:21:03,028
You had heart failure.

372
00:21:03,234 --> 00:21:08,045
This is kind of an insane time
to be criticizing your mom
about being overprotective.

373
00:21:08,167 --> 00:21:15,499
I know. I mean, this is
what makes it even worse.
All of her craziness, it just...

374
00:21:16,906 --> 00:21:19,072
It makes sense now.

375
00:21:19,198 --> 00:21:21,519
Everything's gonna be all right.

376
00:21:22,238 --> 00:21:24,906
I didn't even try to get outside.

377
00:21:26,357 --> 00:21:27,678
I was too scared.

378
00:21:27,762 --> 00:21:28,853
Come on.

379
00:21:39,978 --> 00:21:44,024
Whoa, whoa. Melinda,
please walk back towards me.

380
00:21:44,108 --> 00:21:45,245
Why?

381
00:21:45,924 --> 00:21:47,184
Please?

382
00:21:52,684 --> 00:21:54,525
It feels kind of weird.

383
00:21:56,584 --> 00:21:58,510
It's called steppage gait.

384
00:21:59,005 --> 00:22:00,027
Lewis:
Is it serious?

385
00:22:00,131 --> 00:22:01,637
No, not necessarily.

386
00:22:01,842 --> 00:22:04,223
All right,
stick your leg out, hold it up.

387
00:22:05,946 --> 00:22:09,835
She was under anesthesia
for the biopsy. If she lost oxygen--

388
00:22:09,919 --> 00:22:12,066
C.T. ruled out brain damage.

389
00:22:12,502 --> 00:22:15,634
Put your leg down.
Relax.

390
00:22:18,064 --> 00:22:20,183
Why is her leg
twitching like that?

391
00:22:21,645 --> 00:22:22,803
Fasciculation.

392
00:22:22,887 --> 00:22:24,257
Is that serious?

393
00:22:24,632 --> 00:22:27,612
It's paralysis,
and it's ascending.

394
00:22:27,696 --> 00:22:30,536
She's going to
lose the use of her legs?

395
00:22:34,285 --> 00:22:37,197
To start with.

396
00:22:39,709 --> 00:22:42,375
It's ascending fast.
She can hardly extend her leg now.

397
00:22:42,459 --> 00:22:44,856
At this rate, it'll be up to
her lungs in a matter of days.

398
00:22:46,191 --> 00:22:50,877
So, anaphylaxis,
heart failure, paralysis.

399
00:22:50,935 --> 00:22:54,247
Couldn't put the first two together.
I'm guessing we can't put all three together.

400
00:22:54,312 --> 00:22:55,579
Tick paralysis?

401
00:22:55,783 --> 00:22:57,737
Could also explain the anaphylaxis,
maybe even the--

402
00:22:57,821 --> 00:23:00,580
Penicillin allergy explains
the allergic reaction much better.

403
00:23:00,664 --> 00:23:04,419
Particularly
because tick paralysis is
usually accompanied by a tick.

404
00:23:04,517 --> 00:23:07,309
We did
two comprehensive physicals
looking for insect bites.

405
00:23:07,407 --> 00:23:09,891
Can we put any two
of those together?

406
00:23:09,975 --> 00:23:11,682
How about we stipulate?

407
00:23:11,766 --> 00:23:14,476
You argued that there must be
something to connect all three symptoms,

408
00:23:14,560 --> 00:23:18,154
you mocked us for not figuring it out,
and finally you let us discuss the paralysis

409
00:23:18,238 --> 00:23:20,608
on its own because
it's what's gonna kill her.

410
00:23:20,776 --> 00:23:21,770
Now, it's ascending.

411
00:23:21,873 --> 00:23:24,347
Her MRIs are clean,
so rule out stroke or aneurysm.

412
00:23:24,431 --> 00:23:26,338
- ALS? MS?
- Progression's too quick.

413
00:23:26,397 --> 00:23:28,554
- Spinal lesion from leukemia?
- Too slow.

414
00:23:28,638 --> 00:23:30,083
It's most likely
Guillain-Barre.

415
00:23:30,167 --> 00:23:32,534
She's immunosuppressed.
What about botulism?

416
00:23:32,618 --> 00:23:34,723
Not unless she's been
walking around on her hands
the last couple of days.

417
00:23:34,807 --> 00:23:36,919
Botulism paralysis is
descending, not ascending.

418
00:23:37,003 --> 00:23:37,871
Could be a virus.

419
00:23:37,939 --> 00:23:40,278
West Nile, even polio
with her immune system shot.

420
00:23:40,362 --> 00:23:43,645
Get an LP and
do PCRs for the viruses.

421
00:23:43,724 --> 00:23:46,043
And get an EMG
to check for Guillain-Barre.

422
00:23:46,127 --> 00:23:48,852
Foreman's right. We gotta
find out why she's paralyzed.

423
00:23:51,135 --> 00:23:54,351
But not before staring at me
dumbly for a few seconds.

424
00:24:05,440 --> 00:24:07,730
Foreman:
We ran more tests
on your daughter.

425
00:24:07,834 --> 00:24:10,891
We took a lumbar puncture,
got some spinal fluid.

426
00:24:11,042 --> 00:24:14,978
Then we brought her to the lab
to look for infections that
could be affecting her brain.

427
00:24:17,399 --> 00:24:22,672
We also did an EMG to check
how her muscles and nerves are
responding to electrical impulses.

428
00:24:22,892 --> 00:24:26,709
Unfortunately, her muscles are showing
increased weakness above the knee.

429
00:24:26,793 --> 00:24:28,492
You mean she's getting worse?

430
00:24:28,854 --> 00:24:31,804
The LP and PCRs ruled out
polio and West Nile.

431
00:24:31,869 --> 00:24:33,892
We think it's Guillain-Barre.

432
00:24:33,976 --> 00:24:37,779
The body's immune response
goes haywire and starts
attacking the peripheral nerves.

433
00:24:37,846 --> 00:24:40,640
It causes
muscle weakness and paralysis.

434
00:24:41,233 --> 00:24:42,320
How bad is it?

435
00:24:42,404 --> 00:24:46,881
It's serious, but
Guillain-Barre usually responds
very well to plasmapheresis.

436
00:24:54,160 --> 00:24:56,984
Foreman:
You see, the plasma,
the clear liquid part of her blood,

437
00:24:57,068 --> 00:25:01,437
contains most of the antibodies,
which are overreacting and
attacking her nervous system.

438
00:25:01,627 --> 00:25:06,390
The machine spins her blood
in a centrifuge and separates parts
of the blood based on weight.

439
00:25:06,474 --> 00:25:10,835
White blood cells are the heaviest,
then the red cells, then platelets and plasma.

440
00:25:10,919 --> 00:25:16,797
We discard the stuff that's causing
all the trouble and return the good blood cells
back to her body in a replacement fluid.

441
00:25:16,913 --> 00:25:21,217
If it works, we'll see results
in a couple of days.

442
00:25:28,057 --> 00:25:30,725
You didn't get any messages
for me last week, did you?

443
00:25:30,994 --> 00:25:31,745
Nope.

444
00:25:32,172 --> 00:25:33,120
That's funny.

445
00:25:33,490 --> 00:25:35,878
The guy finally called back.
The place I lost?

446
00:25:36,020 --> 00:25:37,957
He said he left
three voice mails.

447
00:25:38,041 --> 00:25:38,612
Gotta pee.

448
00:25:38,696 --> 00:25:42,762
Which I never got,
if that wasn't clear.

449
00:25:42,913 --> 00:25:44,481
He must be lying.

450
00:25:44,549 --> 00:25:46,447
You wouldn't want
to live with a liar.

451
00:25:46,555 --> 00:25:48,818
- You erased my messages?
- Yup.

452
00:25:48,902 --> 00:25:50,871
Decided I wanted you to stay.

453
00:25:50,955 --> 00:25:52,165
Told you that, didn't I?

454
00:25:52,371 --> 00:25:58,806
You're...miserable, and you're lonely, and
you're gonna trap me here to keep me
every bit as miserable and lonely, too.

455
00:25:58,890 --> 00:26:01,934
- Yeah, and you're
happy, happy, happy.
- Okay.

456
00:26:02,018 --> 00:26:04,951
Hey, I'm obviously going
through a rough patch here.

457
00:26:05,035 --> 00:26:07,784
Wife leaves, tends
to bum somebody out.

458
00:26:08,982 --> 00:26:10,933
Do you know
where my pee went?

459
00:26:13,784 --> 00:26:15,151
You're missing some?

460
00:26:15,235 --> 00:26:18,285
